  <body>
    <sec id="s1">
      <title>Inline Content</title>
      <p>Inline rendering includes <bold>strong text</bold>, <italic>emphasis</italic>, <monospace>monospace</monospace>, <named-content content-type="gene">neurod2</named-content>, <styled-content style-type="underline">styled content</styled-content>, <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig1">Figure 1</xref>, <xref ref-type="table" rid="tbl1">Table 1</xref>, <xref ref-type="sec" rid="s2">the Blocks section</xref>, <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq1">Equation 1</xref>, <xref ref-type="supplementary-material" rid="supp1">Supplementary File 1</xref>, and an external <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://europepmc.org">Europe PMC link</ext-link>.</p>
      <p>Inline TeX math should render here: <inline-formula><tex-math><![CDATA[E = mc^2]]></tex-math></inline-formula>. MathML fallback should remain readable: <inline-formula><mml:math><mml:mi>x</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:math></inline-formula>.</p>
      <p>Inline media marker: <inline-graphic xlink:href="inline-marker.png"/> and inline email <email>xml-reader@example.test</email>.</p>
      <list list-type="bullet">
        <list-item><p>First list item with <italic>formatting</italic>.</p></list-item>
        <list-item><p>Second list item with <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="ref1">citation</xref>.</p></list-item>
      </list>
    </sec>
    <sec id="s2">
